The four people shown in the photograph are low-income residents of Siem Reap Province, Cambodia who are jointly requesting a loan. Mrs. Long R., 43, has been selected as leader by the other group members. Long R. and her husband have been operating a fishing business in and around the Tunle Sap River for more than 10 years, earning an average of $6 per day. This income enables them to support and pay the school fees of their school-aged child. Due to the coming rising water and fishing season, the river is full of fish, but Long lacks equipment to fish and so is requesting a loan. 

There are three other borrowers in this group who have requested a loan as follows: 
Mrs. L., a fishing equipment seller, is asking for a loan to expand her business;
Mrs. L., a fisherwoman, is asking for a loan to buy a machine to support her fishing business;
Mrs. L., a fisherwoman, is asking for a loan to buy fish nets.
